        <!-- Section 1: Introduction -->
        <section>
            <h2>What is Artificial Intelligence?</h2>
            <p>
                Artificial Intelligence (AI) is a way of teaching machines to think and act like humans using computer programs. It helps computers and systems learn from data, figure things out, and even improve their performance without needing step-by-step instructions. AI works by mimicking how humans learn, reason, and solve problems. For example, it can recognize speech, understand images, and even predict future events based on patterns in data.

                We use AI in many areas of our lives without even realizing it. Virtual assistants like Siri and Alexa can answer questions, play music, and remind us of important tasks. AI is also making a big impact in healthcare, where it helps doctors diagnose diseases earlier and create personalized treatments for patients. In transportation, self-driving cars are being developed to make travel safer and easier. Streaming platforms, like Netflix or Spotify, use AI to recommend shows and songs you’ll love based on what you’ve already enjoyed.
                
                What makes AI so exciting is its ability to do things faster and more accurately than humans. It can analyze huge amounts of information in seconds, recognize patterns that are hard for people to spot, and make smart predictions. Imagine cars that can drive themselves, robots that help with surgeries, or AI systems that can predict natural disasters and save lives. AI doesn’t just help us in big ways—it also improves small things, like translating languages or suggesting better routes on a map.
                
                Overall, AI is helping us solve problems, create new inventions, and dream of things that seemed impossible in the past. While there are challenges, like making sure AI is used responsibly, it’s clear that this technology is shaping the future in exciting ways.
                
                
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2: Applications of AI -->
        <section>
            <h2>Applications of AI</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> AI helps in diagnosing diseases and developing personalized treatment plans.</li>
                <li><strong>Transportation:</strong> Self-driving cars and traffic management systems are revolutionizing travel.</li>
                <li><strong>Entertainment:</strong> Streaming platforms use AI to recommend content based on user preferences.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 3: Future of AI -->
        <section>
            <h2>The Future of AI</h2>
            <p>
                As AI continues to evolve, it holds the potential to transform industries and solve some of the world's biggest challenges. 
                However, it also raises ethical concerns, such as bias in algorithms, data privacy issues, and job displacement. The future 
                of AI lies in finding a balance between leveraging its benefits and addressing these challenges responsibly.
            </p>
        </section>

